# How to deploy on GitHub Pages

[Table of Contents]
1. Summary
2. Steps

[Summary]
1. Remote Repository
	1. Create a remote repository on GitHub
	2. Change Source Branch
2. Local Repository
	1. First time commit
		1. Clone the remote repository on GitHub to Local
	2. Subsequent commit
		1. Pull latest changes from remote repository
	3. Make changes into local repository
	4. Add changes
	5. Commit changes
	6. Push changes to remote repository
3. Refresh url
4. Repeat steps 2.2-7

[Steps]
1.1. Create a remote repository on GitHub
1.2. Change Source Branch
	i. Go to Tab "Pages"
	ii. Select a source branch
		- Recommendation
			- Branch: "main"
			- Location: /(root)
	iii. Press Save
2.1. First-time commits
	i. Clone the remote repository on GitHub to Local
		- git clone <website-remote-repository-url>
2.2. Subsequent commits
	i. Pull latest changes from remote repository
		- git pull {remote-repository-url} {branch}
			- git pull origin main
2.3. Make changes into local repository
	- Create index.html
	- Create style.css
	- Create script.js
2.4. Add changes 
	- git add {files/folders/paths}
		- git commit *
			- all
		- git commit . 
			- current folder
2.5. Commit changes
	- git commit -m {commit-message}
		- git commit -m "First change"
2.6. Push changes to remote repository
	- git push -u {remote-repository-url} {branch}
		- git push -u origin main
3. Refresh url
	- {github-name}.github.io/{repository}
4. Repeat steps 2.2-3